'''漫步莎莉园'''（{{lang-en|Down by the Salley Gardens}}，[[爱尔兰语|爱尔兰语]]：''Gort na Saileán''）是[[爱尔兰|爱尔兰]]诗人[[威廉·巴特勒·叶芝|威廉·巴特勒·叶芝]]的一首诗，收录于1889年出版的诗集《{{le|莪相的漫游及其他|The Wanderings of Oisin and Other Poems}}》中。<ref name =Irish>{{cite web| url = http://www.irishmusicdaily.com/down-by-the-salley-gardens| title = Down by the Salley Gardens – tale of unrequited love| accessdate = November 23, 2014| website = irishmusicdaily.com| archive-date = 2020-12-11| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201211154127/https://www.irishmusicdaily.com/down-by-the-salley-gardens| dead-url = no}}</ref>

==译名==
诗名有“柳园里”、“走过柳园”、“莎莉花园”、“走过黄柳园”等多种译名。
==历史==
叶芝在记录中将该诗称为“是对一首老歌进行重现的尝试，老歌来自于{{le|巴利索达尔|Ballisodare}}村一个老农妇记忆中不完整的三条线，她经常唱歌给自己听。”<ref>Quoted in M.H Abrams and Stephen Greenblatt eds., ''The Norton Anthology of English Literature, Vol. 2''. New York: W.W. Norton, 2005. p. 2024.</ref>所谓的老歌或许是民谣《快乐的漫步男孩》（''The Rambling Boys of Pleasure''）<ref>{{cite book|last=Jeffares|first=Alexander|date=1968|title=A Commentary on the Collected Poems of W.B. Yeats (Stanford University Press)|url=https://archive.org/details/commentaryoncoll00jeff}}</ref>，歌词中包含如下句子：
 
:"Down by yon flowery garden my love and I we first did meet.
:I took her in my arms and to her I gave kisses sweet
:She bade me take life easy just as the leaves fall from the tree.
:But I being young and foolish, with my darling did not agree."

这4句与叶芝诗中的第一节非常相似，这也暗示了这就是叶芝所听老妇所唱的那首歌。然而，歌的余下部分则完全不同。

1895年，这首诗首次刊登时，在现有的标题后面还加上了“老歌新唱”（"An Old Song Re-Sung"）这行字。<ref>Ford, Robert, ''W.B.Yeats: A Life'' (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1997), p. 69</ref>

==诗文==
{{listen|filename=Dancing Willow - Demo-CD 2007 04 - Sally gardens.ogg|title=Salley gardens|description=由Dancing Willow演唱|format=[[Ogg|Ogg]]}}
:Down by the salley gardens my love and I did meet;
:She passed the salley gardens with little snow-white feet.
:She bid me take love easy, as the leaves grow on the tree;
:But I, being young and foolish, with her would not agree.

:In a field by the river my love and I did stand,
:And on my leaning shoulder she laid her snow-white hand.
:She bid me take life easy, as the grass grows on the weirs;
:But I was young and foolish, and now am full of tears.<ref>The Collected Poems of W.B. Yeats, (London, Wordsworth Editions) 1994, page 16</ref>

==地点==
据信莎莉园（Salley Gardens）就在{{le|巴利索达尔|Ballisodare}}的河岸边，岸边种植了居民用以盖屋顶的树木。<ref name='McGarry'>{{cite book | last1 = McGarry | first1 = James P | title = Place names in the writings of William Butler Yeats | publisher = Macmillan | year = 1976 | location = London, UK | pages = 79}}</ref><ref name='Jeffares'>{{cite book | last1 = Jeffares | first1 = A. Norman | title = A new commentary on the poems of W.B. Yeats | publisher = Stanford University Press | year = 1984 | location = Stanford,, CA USA | pages = 14}}</ref>“Salley”或“sally”是标准英语词汇“sallow”（黄华柳）的另一种形式。它与意为柳树的爱尔兰词汇''saileach''发音相近。

==配曲==
1909年，诗词被{{le|赫伯特·休斯(作曲家)|Herbert Hughes (musicologist)}}加入了[[AIR_(音乐乐式)|抒情调]]音乐《{{le|穆尔洛赫湖岸|The Moorlough Shore}}》中。<ref name =Irish/>20世纪20年代，作曲家[[丽贝卡·克拉克(作曲家)|丽贝卡·克拉克]]（1886年——1979年）将其加进了自己的音乐。<ref>Jezic, D. P. (1988). Women composers: The lost tradition found (2nd ed., pp. 157-162). New York: The Feminist Press.</ref>作曲家[[约翰·艾尔兰|约翰·艾尔兰]]（1879年——1962年）将诗词配上旋律加进了他作于1929年至1931年的[[声乐套曲|声乐套曲]]《{{le|圣歌与俗歌|Songs Sacred and Profane}}》之中。<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.lieder.net/lieder/assemble_texts.html?SongCycleId=82| title = Songs Sacred and Profane, Song Cycle by John (Nicholson) Ireland| author = Perry, Ted| accessdate = November 23, 2014| website = recmusic.org| archive-date = 2021-01-24| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210124061231/https://www.lieder.net/lieder/assemble_texts.html?SongCycleId=82| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Craggs |first=Stewart R. |title=John Ireland: A Catalogue, Discography and Bibliography: A Source Book |pages=92{{ndash}}93 |date=28 January 2013 |publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd. |edition=2nd |asin=B00AW99HNA }}</ref>1938年，出版了由作曲家{{le|艾弗·格尼|Ivor Gurney}}作曲的歌曲版本。<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.lieder.net/lieder/assemble_texts.html?SongCycleId=7084| title = A First Volume of Ten Songs, Collection by Ivor (Bertie) Gurney (1890 - 1937)| author = Perry, Ted| accessdate = November 23, 2014| website = recmusic.org| archive-date = 2021-01-25| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125015248/https://www.lieder.net/lieder/assemble_texts.html?SongCycleId=7084| dead-url = no}}</ref>1943年，[[本杰明·布里顿|本杰明·布里顿]]为这首诗谱过曲。<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.lieder.net/lieder/get_text.html?TextId=17581| title = Down by the Salley Gardens| author = Perry, Ted| accessdate = November 23, 2014| website = recmusic.org| archive-date = 2020-10-24| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201024030230/https://www.lieder.net/lieder/get_text.html?TextId=17581| dead-url = no}}</ref>1988年，美国作曲家[[约翰·科里利亚诺|约翰·科里利亚诺]]出版了此诗的配乐版本。<ref>{{cite web| title= Three Irish Folksong Settings (1988)| url= http://www.johncorigliano.com/index.php?p=item2&item=103| author= Corigliano, John| website= johncorigliano.com| accessdate= 17 March 2016| archive-date= 2021-04-22| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210422020611/http://www.johncorigliano.com/index.php?p=item2&item=103| dead-url= no}}</ref>

